> Good news! There's no need for a special trip to NYC to enjoy the fantastic flavors of a street cart-style bowl. Our chefs dreamed up this fab vegan version. Fragrant turmeric rice with crunchy almonds and scallions, shawarma-spiced chickpeas, Israeli-style cucumber-tomato salad, and TWO sauces—drizzly hummus and perky hot sauce—all served with warmed pita bread. Now, time to perfect your dipping technique for the optimal saucy and flavor-packed bite.

== Yellow Rice ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #small pot over medium heat. Stir in
@turmeric{1/4%tsp} until combined.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, one of the @veggie stock concentrate{1},
@water{1 1/4%cups}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

== Cucumber-Tomato Salad ==

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Dice @tomato{1}. Quarter @cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into
1/2-inch-thick quarter-moons. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens.

In a #small bowl, combine @hummus{4%tbsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp},
@garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Add @water{1%tsp} at a
time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

In a separate #small bowl, combine tomato, cucumber, half the scallion greens,
juice from one lemon wedge, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

== Chicken & Chickpeas ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels; season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn
off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites, half the @shawarma spice blend{1/2%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chickpeas{} and their liquid and remaining @veggie stock concentrate{2}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until chickpeas are glazed and liquid has mostly
evaporated, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in a squeeze of lemon juice; season with @salt{}
and @pepper{} to taste.

== Pitas & Assembly ==

While chickpeas cook, brush @pita bread{2} all over with a drizzle of @olive oil{},
season with remaining @garlic powder{1 1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Place on a #baking sheet and toast on top rack until softened and warmed
through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Cut pitas into four wedges each.

Fluff rice with a #fork; stir in @sliced almonds{1/2%oz} and remaining
scallion greens. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with chickpeas and salad in separate sections.
Drizzle bowls with hummus sauce and @hot sauce{2%tsp} to taste. Serve with pitas
and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: If you like, scoop up some of the rice, chickpeas, veggies, and sauces
> with the pita and eat it all in one bite!

Slice chicken crosswise. Top rice with chicken along with chickpeas and salad.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.